Slide 3 — The System Design

Headline
The answer is test-driven, small-batch delivery — not “more AI in QA.”

Body copy
	1.	Define requirements as testable behaviors
	2.	Build the smallest slice that satisfies one behavior
	3.	Run automated checks at the right depth
	4.	Route only high-risk changes to heavier human review
	5.	Ship small changes behind flags
	6.	Turn production feedback into the next regression tests

Human vs. machine

Machines own
	•	Linting, typing, static checks
	•	Unit and contract test execution
	•	Regression runs
	•	Basic PR review
	•	Security scans
	•	Release gates on known metrics

Humans own
	•	Requirement quality
	•	Architecture and tradeoffs
	•	High-risk changes
	•	Ambiguous edge cases
	•	Sensitive production judgment

Visual guidance
A simple loop with six numbered steps.
Use one distinction only: Machine-led vs Human-led.

Speaker note / emphasis line
The key shift is not automating everything. It is making each step small, testable, and recoverable.

