Slide 4 — The Delivery Discipline

Headline
Smaller PRs, explicit risk tiers, and right-sized testing.

Body copy
Analysis across large PR datasets shows a consistent pattern: smaller pull requests are reviewed faster and catch more issues, while very large PRs slow review and reduce defect detection. The practical takeaway is simple: keep changes small enough to understand quickly.

Rules of thumb
	•	One behavior per PR
	•	Branch lifetime in hours, not days
	•	Use flags to ship incomplete work safely

Risk tiers

Low risk
Copy changes, UI polish, isolated logic
→ automated review, light testing

Medium risk
Workflow changes, API updates, multi-file logic
→ standard suite plus human review

High risk
Auth, payments, permissions, migrations
→ full suite, senior review, staged rollout

Test layers
	•	Unit — logic and edge cases
	•	Contract — interfaces between services
	•	Integration — critical multi-component flows
	•	E2E — highest-value user journeys only
	•	Release — smoke tests, canary checks, monitoring gates

Visual guidance
