Slide 6 — Three Waves to Get There

Headline
Do not rip and replace. Move in three waves.

Wave 1 — Tighten the current model
Weeks 1–6
	•	Set PR sizing rules
	•	Define risk tiers
	•	Match CI depth to risk
	•	Add clearer acceptance criteria
	•	Establish flaky-test policy

Measure
	•	PR size
	•	Cycle time
	•	Flaky test rate

Wave 2 — Push quality upstream
Months 2–4
	•	Require testable acceptance criteria in PRDs
	•	Pilot behavior-first stories on 1–2 teams
	•	Align PMs and Eng on the smallest releasable slice

Measure
	•	Escaped defects
	•	Rework rate
	•	Review churn

Wave 3 — Automate release safety
Months 3–6
	•	Add browser automation for critical journeys
	•	Introduce feature-flagged delivery
	•	Tie release gates to production thresholds

Measure
	•	Deployment frequency
	•	Rollback rate
	•	Change failure rate

Final takeaway
The roadmap is not “buy more QA tools.”
It is: move from AI-assisted coding to test-driven, small-batch, system-level delivery.

